President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Florida due to the impact of Hurricane Irma. This declaration allows for federal funding to be made available to affected individuals in certain counties. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing, home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid in recovery. Federal funding is also available for emergency work in all 67 counties in the state, as well as for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Justo Hern√°ndez has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. The toll-free phone numbers will be available from 7 a.m. to 10 p.m. seven days a week. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.